The paper is about using neural network language models for information retrieval, which is a subfield of computer science that falls under the category of Information Retrieval (cs.IR). The paper also mentions the use of language models based on neural networks, which is a subfield of natural language processing (NLP) that falls under the category of Computational Linguistics (cs.CL). The paper proposes and studies the use of new neural network models, which involves machine learning techniques and falls under the category of Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI). Finally, the paper mentions the use of distributed representations of words, which is a subfield of neural networks that falls under the category of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE).
